reason.tex:
%text
Strictly speaking, 
\[\dfrac{x^2}{(x^2+4)\cdot(x^2+9)} = \underbrace{\frac{Ax+B}{x^2+4} + \frac{Cx+D}{x^2+9}}_{\text{Always true}}\]
But in this case, notice that if $z = x^2$, then 
%
\begin{align}
\dfrac{x^2}{(x^2 + 4)\cdot (x^2 +9)} &= 
\dfrac{z}{(z+4)\cdot (z+9)} \\
&= \frac{B}{z+4} + \frac{D}{z+9}
\end{align}
